  "body": "### Description\r\nNowadays the `x` and `y` position of `MessageContextMenuView` is assigned in different ways and contexts which makes the code difficult to follow.\r\n\r\nLook for all places where  `messageContextMenu.x` and `y` is assigned by using their related  `messageContextMenu.setXPosition()` or `messageContextMenu.setYPosition()` and replace the **JS code** to **property bindings.**\r\n\r\nReview all components where `MessageContextMenuView` is used like for example `CompactMessageView` or `MessageView` (there are few more).\r\n\r\nTake a look at the complete `MessageContextMenuView` and decide if it can be splited into different specific context menus to clearly have division of responsibilities.",
